This paper investigates the use of emoticons in software development, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves analyzing large amounts of data from issue trackers, which could be categorized as social and information networks (cs.SI) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it explores how developers express emotions through emoticons. Finally, the study involves text analysis, which could be categorized as computational linguistics (cs.CL).
